subSubSection.paragraph:
Telson (
Fig. 11 d
): about 0.9 as long as wide, cleft almost reaching base; lobe subovate, with 1 large subdistal spine-like setae, accompanied with 1 small setae and 2 pairs of long penicillate setae on dorsal surface.

Coloration. Body coloration of alive animals varies from completely white to light yellow (see
Fig. 2 c
).
